{
  "stem": "2435.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was able for three and a half months to stay in that clinic and finish my state exam as a babies' and children's nurse.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mrs.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Bergmann, in 1937, you were 21 years old.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you acquired a profession, that is babies' nurse.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You mentioned that the clinic was-- the head of the clinic was-- A Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--Mr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fockenheim, a-- the Jew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it was like a miracle that Mr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Fockenheim was still there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Actually, around us, you heard about deportation of so and so many friends of my parents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But Fockenheim was still there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Apparently-- I do not really know why.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they never assaulted me or asked me to leave before that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when I left there, I was still able even to work in the Jewish hospital, learning massage and [INAUDIBLE], and physical therapy for a while.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I think that was just one or two months.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was amazing that Herr Fockenheim was still there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But later on, I think right after he was taken away, things began to get much more serious.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my father, seeing that so many of his friends were already deported to Theresienstadt and Auschwitz, and Dachau and Bergen-Belsen, he resumed his efforts to get us out of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he wrote to many friends who were already-- had already immigrated, asking them for letters of recommendation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And amongst them, one of them was Professor Einstein, who had immigrated in 1933.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Einstein wrote.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he contacted the American consulate in Berlin, and asked them to hurry the visa for us, requesting the visa, because it was really the last minute.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But my parents did not get the visa until 1940, in-- in autumn 1940.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I tell you, I think it was known amongst many Christian circles.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
